<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id0dfe3e7b-3a70-11f1-a648-bee82ed8a795" identifier="/us/usc/t20/s6084"><num value="6084">§ 6084.</num><heading> Preemption</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">Nothing in this part is intended to preempt any provision of law of a State or political subdivision of a State that is more restrictive than a provision of this part.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="id0dfe3e7c-3a70-11f1-a648-bee82ed8a795">(<ref href="/us/pl/103/227/tX/s1044">Pub. L. 103–227, title X, § 1044</ref>, <date date="1994-03-31">Mar. 31, 1994</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/108/274">108 Stat. 274</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
</section>
